---
title: Bacon, Asparagus & Grape Tomato Cavatappi with Basil & Parmesan
description: This pasta dish has a quick trick we love: cooking asparagus and grape tomatoes in smoky bacon fat after sizzling bacon to crisp perfection. Toss those veggies with curly cavatappi in creamy basil sauce, then bring it all home with chopped bacon, shredded Parmesan, and a sprinkle of chili flakes for a savory meal that’s sure to satisfy.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65e73fa63251bf1977c05f9e-1ce5140f.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65e8daa8ad357710d5d5528e.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
cuisine: Southern Europe
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 830 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 850 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/bacon-asparagus-and-grape-tomato-cavatappi-65e8daa8ad357710d5d5528e
servings: 2
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Heat a large dry #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning
occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.
> TIP: Add a drizzle of oil if your bacon is not crisping.

Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Reserve 1 TBSP bacon fat
in a small #bowl{}. Wipe out pan with paper towels. Once bacon is cool
enough to handle, roughly chop.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta
cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

While pasta cooks, halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Trim and discard woody bottom ends
from @asparagus{6%ounce}; cut stalks crosswise into 1-inch pieces.

Heat reserved bacon fat and a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for bacon over
medium-high heat. Add tomatoes, asparagus, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until asparagus is bright green, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and add @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @basil paste{1}, ½ cup reserved
pasta cooking water, @butter{2%tablespoon}, and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}.
> For 4 servings, use 1 cup pasta cooking water, 4 TBSP butter, and ½ tsp sugar.

Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until butter has melted,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Add drained cavatappi and toss until thoroughly coated.
> TIP: Add extra splashes of reserved pasta cooking water for saucier pasta.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and top with bacon, @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}(shredded), and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.